choices.text:
the national curfew that happened overnight at midnight for 12 hours instated by the current government. The citizens of Denmark weren't completely over the top happy about it, but everyone followed it when it was announced during the pandemic. I've heard that when it happened a lot of people were out and caught lining the windows and streets. 

We had swine fever around 5 years ago and that made a serious impact in the slaughter of domestic animals throughout Denmark. This caused an increase in price of pork meat for consumers, and was something our economy still feels longterm. Slaughtering pigs is a huge contributor to our economy and our farmers and their crops being affected was unsettling. In general, I feel that Danish agriculture has been on a sharp decrease in the past few years. But I could have gotten the general picture - not the case for every household. 

It also seems like a lot of people are moving to other countries for life, work, or school. I am moving out of the country in 3 months for graduate school. Most of my classmates in my major are considering or are leaving Denmark for another country.

anonymous: Are you finding people are moving out because Denmark is now even more expensive to live in?
